"Implement the following plan:\n\n# Droid Test Suite Assessment\n\n## Context\nAudit of all Factory AI Droid test files to determine whether they're testing meaningful behavior or are useless/redundant.\n\n---\n\n## File-by-File Assessment\n\n### 1. `factoryaidroid_test.go` — Mixed quality (40% trivial, 60% useful)\n\n**Genuinely useful tests:**\n- `TestDetectPresence` — Tests real filesystem behavior with `.factory/` directory\n- `TestReadTranscript` / `TestReadTranscript_MissingFile` — Tests file I/O and error path\n- `TestChunkTranscript_LargeContent` — Tests non-trivial chunking at line boundaries\n- `TestChunkTranscript_RoundTrip` — Tests the critical invariant: chunk + reassemble = original\n- `REDACTED` — Tests JSON parsing with error cases\n- `TestGetSessionDir` — Tests path sanitization logic (non-alphanumeric → `-`)\n- `TestGetSessionDir_EnvOverride` — Tests env var override for testing\n\n**Trivial / nearly useless tests (candidates for removal):**\n- `TestName` — Tests `return agent.AgentNameFactoryAIDroid` (a constant)\n- `TestType` — Tests `return agent.AgentTypeFactoryAIDroid` (a constant)\n- `TestDescription` — Tests `desc != \"\"` (meaningless assertion)\n- `TestGetHookConfigPath` — Tests `return \".factory/settings.json\"` (a string literal)\n- `TestSupportsHooks` — Tests `return true`\n- `TestGetSessionID` — Tests `return input.SessionID` (single field access)\n- `TestReadSession` / `TestWriteSession` — Tests that unimplemented stubs return errors; will need to be deleted when implemented, protects nothing meaningful\n- `TestResolveSessionFile` — Tests `filepath.Join(dir, id+\".jsonl\")` (one-liner)\n- `TestFormatResumeCommand` — Tests `\"droid --session-id \" + sessionID` (string concat)\n- `TestChunkTranscript_SmallContent` — Trivial case (fits in one chunk), redundant with RoundTrip\n- `TestReassembleTranscript_SingleChunk` / `TestReassembleTranscript_MultipleChunks` — Redundant with RoundTrip test\n\n### 2. `lifecycle_test.go` — Solid (all tests are useful)\n\nEvery test validates the critical hook-name → event-type mapping, which is the core contract between the Droid agent and the Entire CLI framework:\n\n- `TestParseHookEvent_SessionStart/TurnStart/TurnEnd/SessionEnd` — Each validates correct event type + field population\n- `TestParseHookEvent_SubagentStart/SubagentEnd` — Tests ToolUseID and SubagentID extraction from structured JSON\n- `TestParseHookEvent_Compaction` — Tests pre-compact hook mapping\n- `TestParseHookEvent_SubagentStop_PassThrough` / `Notification_PassThrough` — Tests that acknowledged-but-no-action hooks correctly return nil\n- `TestParseHookEvent_UnknownHook` — Tests graceful handling of future hooks\n- `TestParseHookEvent_EmptyInput` / `MalformedJSON` — Tests error paths\n\n**Verdict:** No changes needed. Every test validates meaningful behavior.\n\n### 3. `transcript_test.go` — Strongest file (nearly all tests are high-value)\n\n**High-value tests:**\n- `TestParseDroidTranscript_NormalizesEnvelope` — **THE most important Droid test.** Validates the Droid-specific format transformation (outer `type:\"message\"` + inner `role` → normalized `type:role`). Without this, all transcript parsing breaks.\n- `TestParseDroidTranscript_StartLineOffset` — Critical for incremental checkpoint processing\n- `TestParseDroidTranscript_RealDroidFormat` — Integration-style test with tool_use content\n- `TestCalculateTokenUsage_StreamingDeduplication` — Tests critical edge case where streaming creates duplicate message IDs\n- `REDACTED` — Protects against a documented bug where files modified only by subagents get missed\n- `TestExtractAllModifiedFilesFromTranscript_IncludesSubagentFiles` — Tests cross-agent file aggregation with actual filesystem\n- `TestCalculateTotalTokenUsageFromTranscript_PerCheckpoint` — Tests per-checkpoint token calculation at different offsets\n- `TestExtractSpawnedAgentIDs_FromToolResult` — Tests complex multi-layer JSON parsing\n\n**Lower-value but still reasonable:**\n- `TestSerializeTranscript` — Round-trip test, adds some value\n- `TestExtractModifiedFiles_Empty` / `TestCalculateTokenUsage_EmptyTranscript` — Nil/zero boundary tests (low value but harmless)\n\n**Verdict:** No changes needed. Very well-designed test file.\n\n### 4. `hooks_test.go` — Excellent (almost all tests are critical)\n\n**Critical tests (protect against data loss):**\n- `TestInstallHooks_PreservesUserHooksOnSameType` — Prevents nuking user's existing hooks during install\n- `TestInstallHooks_PreservesUnknownHookTypes` — Forward-compatibility with future hook types\n- `TestInstallHooks_PermissionsDeny_PreservesUserRules` — Prevents removing user's security rules\n- `TestInstallHooks_PermissionsDeny_PreservesUnknownFields` — Preserves unknown fields like `ask`\n- `TestUninstallHooks_PreservesUserHooks` — Prevents data loss during uninstall\n- `TestUninstallHooks_PreservesUserDenyRules` — Prevents data loss of security rules\n- `TestUninstallHooks_PreservesUnknownHookTypes` — Forward-compatibility during uninstall\n\n**Important functional tests:**\n- `TestInstallHooks_FreshInstall` — Validates all 7 hooks with correct commands\n- `TestInstallHooks_Idempotent` — Prevents hook duplication on re-enable\n- `TestInstallHooks_LocalDev` — Validates dev-mode command format\n- `TestInstallHooks_Force` — Tests force-reinstall path\n- `TestUninstallHooks` / `TestUninstallHooks_RemovesDenyRule` — Clean uninstall paths\n\n**Verdict:** No changes needed. Excellent coverage of critical data-preservation behavior.\n\n### 5. `setup_factoryai_hooks_test.go` (integration) — Useful smoke tests\n\nBoth tests exercise the full CLI command path (`entire enable --agent factoryai-droid`). Useful for catching integration issues that unit tests miss.\n\n---\n\n## Key Gaps (Missing Tests)\n\n### Not tested at all:\n1. **`ExtractPrompts()`** — Parses user content from transcript and strips IDE context tags. Non-trivial logic, completely untested.\n2. **`ExtractSummary()`** — Finds last assistant text message. Completely untested.\n3. **Subagent token aggregation with actual files** — `TestCalculateTotalTokenUsageFromTranscript_PerCheckpoint` passes `\"\"` for subagentsDir every time. No test validates that subagent tokens are correctly summed from real files.\n4. **Malformed JSONL line handling** — The parser silently skips bad lines, but this isn't tested (what happens with `{\"broken json` mid-transcript?).\n5. **`HookNames()` / `GetHookNames()`** — Returns the list of 9 hook verbs. If a hook is accidentally removed from this list, no test catches it.\n\n---\n\n## Recommendations\n\n### Remove (trivial, zero risk of regression):\n- `TestName`, `TestType`, `TestDescription`\n- `TestGetHookConfigPath`, `TestSupportsHooks`\n- `TestGetSessionID`\n- `TestReadSession`, `TestWriteSession`\n- `TestFormatResumeCommand`, `TestResolveSessionFile`\n- `TestChunkTranscript_SmallContent` (covered by RoundTrip)\n- `TestReassembleTranscript_SingleChunk`, `TestReassembleTranscript_MultipleChunks` (covered by RoundTrip)\n\n### Add:\n1. **`TestExtractPrompts`** — Test prompt extraction from Droid transcript (user messages, IDE tag stripping)\n2. **`TestExtractSummary`** — Test last-assistant-message extraction\n3. **`TestCalculateTotalTokenUsageFromTranscript_WithSubagentFiles`** — Create actual subagent JSONL files and verify tokens are aggregated\n4. **`TestParseDroidTranscript_MalformedLines`** — Verify that a transcript with some broken JSON lines still parses the valid lines correctly\n5. **`TestGetHookNames`** — Validate the hook list contains all expected 9 verbs (protects against accidental removal)\n\n### No changes needed:\n- `lifecycle_test.go` — All useful\n- `hooks_test.go` — All useful\n- `transcript_test.go` — All useful (except note the gaps above)\n- Integration test — Useful as-is\n\n---\n\n## Verification\nAfter changes:\n```bash\nmise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci\n```\n\n\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (